Later years ==
Eleonora and Ethel Olson were originally from Chicago, but by the 1920s they and their mother were living in Minneapolis.
They stopped touring in 1923 when Ethel married Dr. Reuben M. Pederson.
In 1925 the Olson Sisters published a collection of their Norwegian dialect stories called Yust for Fun.
A second edition was printed in 1929.
Yust for Fun was republished in 1979 with a new introduction, photographs and biographical information.
